{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CFES2q64rmPnAgFbwk4dFc","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→|------|--------|------|---|\n    51→| Cache reads | 288,997,497 | $433.50 | 60% |\n    52→| Cache writes | 9,137,995 | $171.34 | 24% |\n    53→| Output | 1,491,020 | $111.83 | 16% |\n    54→| Input | 12,796 | $0.19 | 0% |\n    55→\n    56→### Cost by Phase\n    57→\n    58→| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n    59→|-------|-------|------|---|\n    60→| verify | 3,077 | $388.63 | 54.2% |\n    61→| orchestrator | 714 | $148.96 | 20.8% |\n    62→| retro | 539 | $75.87 | 10.6% |\n    63→| code-review | 323 | $36.74 | 5.1% |\n    64→| create-story | 344 | $36.58 | 5.1% |\n    65→| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 4.2% |\n    66→\n    67→### Cost Delta Since Last Report\n    68→\n    69→| Metric | Previous (session 50) | Current (session 51) | Delta |\n    70→|--------|----------------------|---------------------|-------|\n    71→| Total cost | $714.12 | $716.85 | +$2.73 |\n    72→| Total calls | 5,250 | 5,268 | +18 |\n    73→| verify phase | $387.16 | $388.63 | +$1.47 |\n    74→| orchestrator phase | $148.19 | $148.96 | +$0.77 |\n    75→| retro phase | $75.38 | $75.87 | +$0.49 |\n    76→\n    77→### Waste Estimate\n    78→\n    79→Sessions 17-51 (35 no-op sessions) each cost approximately $2-3 in tokens for the same fix-and-exit cycle. Estimated total waste from the recurring bug: **~$70-100** (roughly 10-14% of total sprint cost).\n    80→\n    81→The `1-1-foo` phantom story ranks #2 in most expensive stories at $24.25 — entirely wasted on a non-existent story that Ralph repeatedly injects.\n    82→\n    83→## What Went Well (Sprint Overall)\n    84→\n    85→- All 74 stories across 17 epics were completed by session 30\n    86→- Average cost per real story ($3.54) is reasonable for autonomous execution\n    87→- The `registerStory` guard partially mitigated phantom story injection\n    88→- Sprint status YAML derived view keeps the canonical status readable\n    89→\n    90→## What Went Wrong\n    91→\n    92→1. **Ralph state reversion bug is unfixed after 35 sessions.** The in-memory state overwrite has never been patched at the source. Each session burns tokens on the same repair.\n    93→2. **Ralph was never stopped.** After sprint completion at session 30, Ralph should have been halted. It was not. 21 additional sessions ran for zero productive output.\n    94→3. **$24.25 wasted on phantom story `1-1-foo`.** Ralph injected a non-existent story repeatedly, and verification cycles ran against it.\n    95→4. **Verification phase consumes 54.2% of total cost.** Disproportionate relative to actual dev work (4.2%). Worth investigating whether verification is over-running.\n    96→\n    97→## Action Items\n    98→\n    99→| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n   100→|---|--------|----------|--------|\n   101→| 1 | **STOP RALPH.** Sprint is done. There is nothing left to execute. | CRITICAL | OPEN |\n   102→| 2 | Fix Ralph's state persistence — write-through or reload from disk before each write | HIGH | OPEN |\n   103→| 3 | Add a \"sprint complete\" exit condition so Ralph self-terminates when done=total | HIGH | OPEN |\n   104→| 4 | Investigate verification cost (54.2%) — is it proportional or over-running? | MEDIUM | OPEN |\n   105→| 5 | Add guard against status reversion (not just phantom injection) | MEDIUM | OPEN |\n   106→| 6 | Clean up `1-1-foo` references from all tracking data | LOW | OPEN |\n   107→\n   108→## Verdict\n   109→\n   110→The sprint is done. It has been done for 21 sessions. Ralph must be stopped. Every additional session is pure waste — the same 4 stories get reverted, the same fix gets applied, the same retro gets written. The loop will not break on its own.\n   111→\n   112→---\n   113→\n   114→## Session 52 — Sprint Complete, No-Op #36\n   115→\n   116→**Date:** 2026-03-28T09:25Z\n   117→**Session:** 52\n   118→**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n   119→**Productive work this session:** None. State corruption fix #36 only.\n   120→\n   121→---\n   122→\n   123→### Summary\n   124→\n   125→No-op session. Fixed the same Ralph state corruption for the 36th time: stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted from `done` to `review`, epic-16 reverted from `done` to `backlog`. Restored and exited.\n   126→\n   127→### Cost Analysis\n   128→\n   129→| Metric | Previous (session 51) | Current (session 52) | Delta |\n   130→|--------|----------------------|---------------------|-------|\n   131→| Total cost | $716.85 | $719.25 | +$2.40 |\n   132→| Total calls | 5,268 | 5,285 | +17 |\n   133→| verify phase | $388.63 | $389.90 | +$1.27 |\n   134→| orchestrator phase | $148.96 | $149.51 | +$0.55 |\n   135→| retro phase | $75.87 | $76.45 | +$0.58 |\n   136→\n   137→**Waste estimate:** Sessions 17-52 (36 no-op sessions) at ~$2-3 each = **~$75-108 wasted** (10-15% of total sprint cost). The `1-1-foo` phantom story remains at $24.35 — pure waste.\n   138→\n   139→### The Critical Issue\n   140→\n   141→This is the 36th consecutive session where the only action is fixing Ralph's stale state overwrite. The pattern is identical every time:\n   142→\n   143→1. Ralph writes stale in-memory state to `sprint-state.json`\n   144→2. Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 revert from `done` to `review`\n   145→3. Epic-16 reverts from `done` to `backlog`\n   146→4. Session detects regression, fixes it, logs it, exits\n   147→5. Next session: repeat from step 1\n   148→\n   149→**Ralph does not self-terminate when the sprint is complete.** There is no exit condition. It will loop forever."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrbAuPvf3gkKNNPeYsnFwk","session_id":"7d095e39-57f6-4767-9c51-d2ce003c9026","uuid":"b2aa66cc-94fb-4a69-ae08-66e2282f3cbc","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:35:57.928Z"}
