{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RNFump8GxwEeTfKjXm9YFX","type":"tool_result","content":"  4600→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  4601→\n  4602→- **Ralph state corruption (P0):** 35+ consecutive no-op sessions caused by the same in-memory state overwrite bug. Ralph's `status.json` still shows `stories_completed: 70` and `stories_remaining: 4`. Every session burns orchestrator tokens detecting and fixing this.\n  4603→- **No sprint-complete exit:** Ralph has no condition to stop looping when all stories are done, causing infinite no-op sessions.\n  4604→- **Cost waste from no-ops:** Estimated $150-250 spent on orchestrator overhead across 35+ sessions that did zero productive work.\n  4605→- **\"Unknown\" cost attribution:** 25.9% of total cost ($226.45) is unattributed. Without knowing what drives this, optimization is blind.\n  4606→- **Retro cost creep:** At $102.99 (11.8%), retrospective generation is expensive relative to actual development ($30.07). The retro file is now 4,491 lines — each new retro pays to read the entire file via context window.\n  4607→\n  4608→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  4609→\n  4610→- **State writes need monotonic versioning.** Ralph's read-modify-write loop without version checking is the textbook example of a lost-update bug. Every state write should include a version counter and reject stale writes.\n  4611→- **Sprint-complete must be a hard exit.** Once all stories are `done`, the orchestrator should exit immediately — not enter another loop iteration that loads stale state and \"fixes\" it again.\n  4612→- **Retro file growth is a cost multiplier.** A 4,491-line retro file means every subsequent retro pays for the full context. Consider archiving per-session retros into separate files or using a rolling window.\n  4613→- **Subagent guidelines should mandate single test capture.** Three out of four verification subagents ran `npm test` twice. A one-line guideline (\"capture test output once, filter from capture\") would save ~170 lines of output per verification.\n  4614→- **File read deduplication matters.** `harness-run.md` was read 8 times across two subagents working on the same story. A shared read cache or explicit \"read once, reference by line\" pattern would reduce this.\n  4615→\n  4616→## 7. Action Items\n  4617→\n  4618→| Priority | Action | Status |\n  4619→|----------|--------|--------|\n  4620→| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CRITICAL — 35+ occurrences, estimated $150-250 waste |\n  4621→| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CRITICAL — stops burning sessions |\n  4622→| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4623→| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($226.45, 25.9%) to specific phases/activities | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4624→| **P1** | Archive retro file — split into per-session files or implement rolling window to stop context growth | NEW |\n  4625→| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD — 3/4 verifications ran npm test twice |\n  4626→| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: deduplicate file reads across review+verification for same story | NEW |\n  4627→| **P2** | Fix 5 pre-existing BATS failures in all_tasks_complete suite | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4628→| **P3** | Clean up legacy `black.box` references in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n  4629→| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35 attributed cost) | CARRY FORWARD |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrbAuPvf3gkKNNPeYsnFwk","session_id":"7d095e39-57f6-4767-9c51-d2ce003c9026","uuid":"e113c500-5a32-4bd8-b648-d961b7d197d7","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:36:03.868Z"}
