{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013C7zvreyiTUNHVWuT5hHbn","type":"tool_result","content":"  4550→\n  4551→| Phase | Cost | % | Observation |\n  4552→|-------|------|---|-------------|\n  4553→| verify | $467.21 | 53.4% | Dominant cost center — verification is the most expensive phase by far |\n  4554→| orchestrator | $193.95 | 22.2% | Includes 35+ no-op sessions worth of state detection and fixing |\n  4555→| retro | $102.99 | 11.8% | Retrospective generation is surprisingly expensive |\n  4556→| code-review | $43.15 | 4.9% | Efficient — catches real bugs at low cost |\n  4557→| create-story | $37.05 | 4.2% | Story creation cost is reasonable |\n  4558→| dev-story | $30.07 | 3.4% | Actual development is the cheapest phase — good ratio |\n  4559→\n  4560→### Cost by Tool\n  4561→\n  4562→| Tool | Cost | % | Note |\n  4563→|------|------|---|------|\n  4564→| Bash | $288.98 | 33.0% | Largest — test execution and git commands |\n  4565→| Read | $185.14 | 21.2% | File reading dominates due to large context windows |\n  4566→| Edit | $129.20 | 14.8% | Code modification |\n  4567→| Agent | $79.92 | 9.1% | Subagent dispatch overhead |\n  4568→| Skill | $74.64 | 8.5% | Skill invocations |\n  4569→\n  4570→### Subagent-Level Token Breakdown (from Session Issues Log)\n  4571→\n  4572→Aggregated across 8 subagent runs (4 code reviews + 4 verifications) from earlier today:\n  4573→\n  4574→| Metric | Code Reviews (4) | Verifications (4) | Total |\n  4575→|--------|-----------------|-------------------|-------|\n  4576→| Total tool calls | 86 | 60 | 146 |\n  4577→| Bash calls | 24 | 31 | 55 |\n  4578→| Read calls | 37 | 20 | 57 |\n  4579→| Grep calls | 21 | 12 | 33 |\n  4580→| Edit calls | 11 | 3 | 14 |\n  4581→\n  4582→**Key observations from subagent token reports:**\n  4583→- **Repeated file reads:** `harness-run.md` was read 8 times across the 16-5 code review and verification subagents (5 + 3). A single cached read would suffice.\n  4584→- **Redundant test runs:** 3 of 4 verification subagents ran `npm test` twice (once full, once filtered). Estimated waste: ~170 lines of redundant output per verification.\n  4585→- **Code review is lean:** Average 21.5 tool calls per review. Most reads were unique files (10-14 unique per review).\n  4586→- **Verification is Bash-heavy:** 7-10 Bash calls per verification vs 3-8 for code reviews. Verifications spend most tokens on test execution output.\n  4587→\n  4588→### \"Unknown\" Cost Bucket\n  4589→\n  4590→The `unknown` story bucket remains the largest at $226.45 (25.9%). This likely represents orchestrator overhead, state management, retro generation, and no-op session costs that are not attributed to any specific story.\n  4591→\n  4592→## 4. What Went Well\n  4593→\n  4594→- **Sprint complete: 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics.** Full delivery.\n  4595→- **Code review quality:** Caught 1 HIGH, 9 MEDIUM bugs across 4 stories. All MEDIUM+ fixed in the same pass. Zero stories sent back for rework.\n  4596→- **First-pass verification:** All 4 stories passed on first attempt. 41/41 total ACs passed.\n  4597→- **Coverage maintained:** 96.85% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor throughout.\n  4598→- **Cost efficiency for actual development:** dev-story phase is only 3.4% of total cost. The harness invests heavily in quality gates (verify + code-review = 58.3%) which is the correct trade-off.\n  4599→\n  4600→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  4601→\n  4602→- **Ralph state corruption (P0):** 35+ consecutive no-op sessions caused by the same in-memory state overwrite bug. Ralph's `status.json` still shows `stories_completed: 70` and `stories_remaining: 4`. Every session burns orchestrator tokens detecting and fixing this.\n  4603→- **No sprint-complete exit:** Ralph has no condition to stop looping when all stories are done, causing infinite no-op sessions.\n  4604→- **Cost waste from no-ops:** Estimated $150-250 spent on orchestrator overhead across 35+ sessions that did zero productive work."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrbAuPvf3gkKNNPeYsnFwk","session_id":"7d095e39-57f6-4767-9c51-d2ce003c9026","uuid":"fa0421f4-c866-4260-af58-f76b394dfdef","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:36:13.587Z"}
