{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HoGe5scm1U4ADxVZJB3UwW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MVhr8ySbtqXBBGSzN5thLB","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md","old_string":"| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35 attributed cost) | CARRY FORWARD |","new_string":"| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35 attributed cost) | CARRY FORWARD |\n\n---\n\n# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-28 (Ralph Loop #13)\n\n**Timestamp:** 2026-03-28T12:36Z\n**Ralph loop:** 13\n**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n**Productive work this session:** None. State corruption detected and restored from git.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Session Summary\n\nThis was Ralph loop #13. The sprint has been fully complete (74/74 stories, 16/16 epics) since earlier today. This loop discovered that the working tree's `sprint-state.json` had been corrupted — stories 16-7 and 16-8 were reverted from `done` back to `review`. The committed version in git was correct, so the state was restored from git. No new implementation work was performed.\n\nThe session issues log contains entries from loops ~8-12, covering stories 16-5 through 16-8 — the final four stories of epic 16. All four passed code review and verification on their first attempt.\n\n### Stories from this Ralph run (loops 8-13)\n\n| Story | Outcome | Code Review | Verification |\n|-------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| 16-5 (rewrite harness-run verification dispatch) | Done | 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM fixed | 7/7 ACs PASS |\n| 16-6 (update create-story tier criteria) | Done | 1 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM fixed | 10/10 ACs PASS |\n| 16-7 (update knowledge and enforcement docs) | Done | 0 HIGH, 4 MEDIUM fixed | 12/12 ACs PASS |\n| 16-8 (update all tests) | Done | 0 bugs | 12/12 ACs PASS |\n| Loop 13 (this loop) | No-op | N/A | N/A — state restored from git |\n\n**Total ACs verified across loops 8-12:** 41/41 (100% first-pass success)\n\n## 2. Issues Analysis\n\n### Issues from session log (categorized)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed during code review (8 total):**\n- 1 HIGH: AC2 test false-pass risk in 16-6 (fixed with Given/When/Then validation)\n- 9 MEDIUM across 3 stories: indexOf guard, DRY violation, fragile section coupling (16-5); missing escalate tier test, weak AC8 assertions, silent empty-string fallback x2 (16-7)\n- All HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in-session. None required rework.\n\n**Known LOW issues deferred (out of scope):**\n- Section ordering mismatch in harness-run.md routing table\n- String-matching test brittleness (inherent to prompt file testing)\n- Legacy terms (black.box) in patches/AGENTS.md, patches/retro/enforcement.md, src/templates/verify-prompt.ts\n- classifyTier barrel re-export not tested through index.ts\n- Story line references will drift over time\n- Test count docs drift\n- No explicit runtime>test priority test in classifyTier\n\n**Pre-existing failures (not introduced by this sprint):**\n- 5 BATS failures in `all_tasks_complete` suite — unrelated to epic 16 work\n\n**State corruption (recurring):**\n- `sprint-state.json` in working tree had stories 16-7, 16-8 reverted from `done` to `review`\n- Committed version was correct — restored via git checkout\n- Root cause: Ralph's in-memory state overwrites disk state on loop iteration\n\n## 3. Cost Analysis\n\n### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n\n| Metric | Previous | Current | Delta |\n|--------|----------|---------|-------|\n| Total API-equivalent cost | $874.42 | $876.13 | +$1.71 |\n| Total API calls | 6,363 (est.) | 6,381 | +18 |\n| Average cost per story | ~$4.10 | $4.11 | +$0.01 |\n\n### Cost by Phase (cumulative)\n\n| Phase | Cost | % | Delta from previous |\n|-------|------|---|---------------------|\n| verify | $467.21 | 53.3% | +$0.00 (no new verifications) |\n| orchestrator | $194.98 | 22.3% | +$1.03 |\n| retro | $103.25 | 11.8% | +$0.26 |\n| code-review | $43.57 | 5.0% | +$0.42 |\n| create-story | $37.05 | 4.2% | +$0.00 |\n| dev-story | $30.07 | 3.4% | +$0.00 |\n\n### Cost by Tool (cumulative top 5)\n\n| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |\n|------|-------|------|---|\n| Bash | 2,355 | $289.63 | 33.1% |\n| Read | 1,337 | $185.40 | 21.2% |\n| Edit | 999 | $129.20 | 14.7% |\n| Agent | 614 | $80.18 | 9.2% |\n| Skill | 217 | $74.91 | 8.6% |\n\n### Most Expensive Stories (top 5)\n\n| Story | Cost | % | Note |\n|-------|------|---|------|\n| unknown | $227.37 | 26.0% | Unattributed overhead |\n| 16-5 (harness-run dispatch) | $78.78 | 9.0% | Most complex story in epic 16 |\n| 1-1-foo (phantom) | $24.35 | 2.8% | Pure waste — phantom story |\n| 14-5 (stack-aware verify) | $23.63 | 2.7% | |\n| 14-4 (observability backend) | $22.13 | 2.5% | |\n\n### Subagent-Level Token Breakdown (from session issues log)\n\nAggregated across 8 subagent runs (4 code reviews + 4 verifications) for stories 16-5 through 16-8:\n\n| Metric | Code Reviews (4) | Verifications (4) | Total |\n|--------|-----------------|-------------------|-------|\n| Total tool calls | 86 | 60 | 146 |\n| Bash calls | 24 | 31 | 55 |\n| Read calls | 37 | 20 | 57 |\n| Grep calls | 21 | 12 | 33 |\n| Edit calls | 11 | 3 | 14 |\n\n**Subagent-level observations:**\n- `harness-run.md` was read 8 times across 16-5's code review (5x) and verification (3x). A single cached read would suffice.\n- 3 of 4 verification subagents ran `npm test` twice (once full, once filtered for summary). ~170 lines of redundant output per occurrence.\n- Code review averaged 21.5 tool calls each — lean and efficient.\n- Verification was Bash-heavy (7-10 Bash calls vs 3-8 for code reviews), driven by test execution.\n- 16-8 code review was the most read-intensive (14 unique files, 14 total reads) but had zero redundancy.\n- 16-7 verification was Grep-heavy (10 Grep calls) for checking term replacements across the codebase.\n\n### Waste Estimate\n\n| Category | Estimated Waste |\n|----------|----------------|\n| No-op sessions (36+ across all loops) | ~$75-110 |\n| `1-1-foo` phantom story | $24.35 |\n| Redundant test runs (3/4 verifications) | ~$1-2 |\n| Redundant file reads (harness-run.md 8x) | ~$0.50 |\n| **Total estimated waste** | **~$100-137** |\n\n## 4. What Went Well\n\n- **100% first-pass verification.** All 4 stories (16-5 through 16-8) passed code review and verification without rework. 41/41 ACs passed.\n- **Code review caught real bugs.** 1 HIGH (false-pass risk) and 9 MEDIUM issues found and fixed in-pass. The review gate is earning its cost.\n- **Coverage maintained at 96.85%.** All 158 files above 80% floor. No regressions.\n- **Sprint fully complete.** 74/74 stories, 16/16 epics delivered.\n- **State corruption was recoverable.** The committed git version was correct, allowing a simple `git checkout` restore. The write-back-to-disk bug did not corrupt the committed record.\n- **Lean code reviews.** Average 21.5 tool calls per review, with minimal redundancy in 16-8 (zero redundant reads).\n\n## 5. What Went Wrong\n\n- **Ralph state corruption persists.** The in-memory state overwrite bug continues. This loop saw stories 16-7 and 16-8 reverted. The `registerStory` guard prevents phantom story injection but does not prevent status reversion.\n- **Ralph does not self-terminate.** No sprint-complete exit condition exists. Loop 13 ran despite having nothing to do.\n- **Unattributed cost is the single largest bucket.** At $227.37 (26.0%), the \"unknown\" story bucket is larger than any real story. This needs attribution.\n- **Retro cost continues to grow.** At $103.25 (11.8%), retrospective generation costs more than actual development ($30.07). The retro file is now 4,629 lines — each new retro pays to read the entire thing.\n- **Verification phase dominance.** At 53.3% of total cost, verification is 15.7x more expensive than dev-story. Some of this is justified (rigorous quality gates), but the ratio warrants investigation.\n\n## 6. Lessons Learned\n\n- **First-pass success is achievable.** 41/41 ACs across 4 stories with zero rework proves the dev-then-review-then-verify pipeline works when story specs are clear.\n- **State writes need monotonic versioning.** This is the same lesson as every prior retro. Ralph's read-modify-write loop without version checking causes lost updates.\n- **Sprint-complete must be a hard exit.** Repeated across every retro entry. Ralph needs `if (done === total) exit(0)` at the top of each loop.\n- **Retro file growth is a cost multiplier.** At 4,629 lines, the file is the single largest context cost per retro session. Archiving old entries to separate files would cut this significantly.\n- **Subagent file read deduplication would save tokens.** The harness-run.md file was read 8 times across two subagents for the same story. A shared context or \"read once\" pattern would help.\n\n## 7. Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Status |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CRITICAL — 36+ occurrences |\n| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CRITICAL — each loop wastes ~$1.50-3 |\n| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($227.37, 26.0%) to specific phases/activities | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Archive retro file — split into per-session files or rolling window (4,629 lines and growing) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: deduplicate file reads across review+verification for same story | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Fix 5 pre-existing BATS failures in all_tasks_complete suite | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up legacy `black.box` references in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35) | CARRY FORWARD |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":735,"cache_read_input_tokens":37623,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":735,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrbAuPvf3gkKNNPeYsnFwk","session_id":"7d095e39-57f6-4767-9c51-d2ce003c9026","uuid":"95750cd1-785a-4b30-920f-c8e18c32fbce"}
